<HEADLINE>
FT  21 MAY 94 / Gatt air talks to restart
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By FRANCES WILLIAMS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   GENEVA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The US, the European Union and other members of the 22-strong Gatt civil
aircraft committee agreed on Thursday to resume talks in July on a
replacement for the Gatt's 1979 code of fair trade practice with the aim of
reaching a deal by the end of this year, reports Frances Williams from
Geneva.
The US wants any new accord to be limited to 'multilateralising' its 1992
bilateral pact with the EU which puts a cap on subsidies for the European
Airbus. The EU and most other committee members are insisting that the new
agreement cover all types of civil aircraft and components, and all forms of
state support including indirect assistance through space and military
research contracts as practised by Washington.
