<HEADLINE>
FT  21 MAY 94 / Briefcase, Q&amp;A: Transferring securities
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
With reference to EU bearer securities (ie, BASK AG shares), would you
please clarify the following points:
1. If held by the trustees of a company profit-sharing scheme, can they be
transferred at the end of the five-year term into a single company personal
equity plan?
2. Is it a legal requirement for them to be held in a custodian account at a
bank?
3. Is it true that the collection of dividends is not difficult and involves
only a bit more paperwork?
4. Would you expect to pay a fee, however small, to the custodian to get
physical possession of shares held for five years in a company
profit-sharing scheme?
1. No. 2. No. 3. In our opinion, the answer is No for most people. 4. Yes,
if the sponsoring employer has not undertaken to meet such expenses.
