<HEADLINE>
FT  21 MAY 94 / World Stock Markets: South Africa
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Johannesburg posted steady late-afternoon gains as shares rallied in
response to a stronger gold price and a general improvement in sentiment.
The overall index finished 34 better at 5,474, industrials rose 62 to 6,621
and golds collected 22 to 1,908.
A bounce in Remb Beheer after hefty losses on Thursday helped the mood. The
tobacco stock rose R3.75 to R20.75 after a R7 fall on Thursday after ANC
health officials proposed a 100 per cent rise in cigarette prices.
