FT  21 MAY 94 / London Stock Exchange: Equity futures and options trading
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOEL KIBAZO
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Stock index futures gave up the early advance as dealers followed the
retreat in both UK and US bonds, writes Joel Kibazo.
The June contract on the FT-SE 100 closed at 3,121, down 4 on its previous
close and at a 4 point discount to cash. Volume remained low reaching 10,306
contracts by the close.
Turnover in the traded options jumped to 47,439 lots of which 17,916 was
dealt in the FT-SE 100 option and 3,022 in the Euro FT-SE option. BT was the
busiest stock option with a total of 4,659 contracts traded.
