FT  21 MAY 94 / International Company News: Williams turns down Dollars 2bn
bid for WilTel
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARTIN DICKSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Williams Companies, the diversified energy group, yesterday rejected a
Dollars 2bn offer from LDDS Communications, an acquisitive US
telecommunications group, to buy its subsidiary WilTel, which runs the
nation's fourth-largest long-distance network.
However, Williams's board said it had authorised management to explore other
forms of co-operation with LDDS. Management was also looking at possible
alliances with one or more other partners.
LDDS, which announced its offer earlier this month, is a long-distance
reseller, buying access to long-distance lines in bulk and reselling the
access at a profit.
It is WilTel's second-largest customer, and has been negotiating a new,
long-term contract for services.
