FT  21 MAY 94 / UK Company News: Fenner ends search for chief executive
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW BAXTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Fenner, the Hull-based industrial group, yesterday announced it was
promoting Mr Mark Abrahams, 38, from finance director to chief executive
with immediate effect.
The announcement ends a five-month search by Fenner and Mr Colin Cooke, its
non-executive chairman, for a chief executive. In December, Mr Julian
Bigden, the former managing director, returned to his previous job running
Fenner's US polymers operation.
Mr Cooke said in March that he had three candidates in mind for the job of
chief executive, and it was thought that the appointee would come from
outside the company.
However, in a short statement yesterday Fenner said that since Mr Abrahams
joined the board in 1990 on his appointment as finance director, he had made
a considerable contribution to the restructuring of the group's finances and
its return to a more profitable performance.
Mr Cooke said yesterday that Mr Abrahams was the best of the three
candidates for the job. 'He knows Fenner well, is a strategic thinker, and
has all the attributes we were looking for.'
Mr Cooke and Mr Abrahams have worked together closely in the past year in
the restructuring of the company. The search is now on for a new finance
director.
</TEXT>
