<HEADLINE>
FT  21 MAY 94 / Letters to the Editor: Bias to fee-based advisers who are
weak on specifics
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr JOHN DONOVAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Your excellent series on fee-based financial advisers (Weekend: Finance
and the Family) by Joanna Slaughter was perhaps too heavily biased in their
favour.
Commission earners may be over-anxious for clients to deal or buy a product
but fee-earners are primarily motivated by a desire to get 'funds under
management'. What happens to those funds is as often a matter of luck as
judgment.
Ms Slaughter may or may not have noticed that fee-earners tend to be strong
on generalities but weak on specifics. Commission earners seem to be more
market-oriented and this may give their clients the edge when it comes to
bottom line performance.
John Donovan,
17a La Pleta,
Ordino,
Principality of Andorra
