FT  21 MAY 94 / Charges on lorry deaths ruled out
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The operator of the lorry which ran out of control and killed six people at
Sowerby Bridge, West Yorkshire, will not face prosecution for corporate
manslaughter.
The Crown Prosecution Service said there was insufficient evidence against
Fewston Transport, of Skipton, North Yorkshire, although the inquest into
the deaths had recorded a verdict of unlawful killing. The company is due in
court next week to face charges of using a lorry with defective brakes after
its vehicle hit a van on a hill and crashed into a row of shops and houses.
Both drivers died along with three women and a two-year-old girl.
