FT  21 MAY 94 / BA flights may face disruption
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Unions yesterday forecast disruption next weekend for travellers using
British Airways because of industrial action among staff, including check-in
and baggage supervisors.
Some 2,530 of the 12,000 administrative workers at BA, where about half the
total are union members, voted for action short of a strike, with 1,467 in
favour and 1,039 against. The dispute is over a number of issues, including
changes to terms and conditions of employment.
The TGWU general union said talks with BA were scheduled for Monday, but if
the issues were not resolved action would begin next weekend. It had given
management the seven-day notice of industrial action required by law. BA
said it was not anticipating disruption at this stage because discussions
were scheduled for next week.
