<HEADLINE>
FT  21 MAY 94 / Debt may be written off
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By FRANCES WILLIAMS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   GENEVA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Further debt relief for the world's poorest countries could be in the offing
following a two-day meeting in Geneva of finance ministry officials from the
main creditor nations, writes Frances Williams in Geneva. British officials
said yesterday there was 'widespread support' for Britain's call for full
implementation of the so-called Trinidad terms. These involve an immediate
write-off of more than half the debt owed to governments by highly-indebted
low-income countries, mostly in Africa. Total public bilateral debt owed by
severely-indebted low-income countries topped Dollars 110bn in 1992, up from
Dollars 80bn in 1986.
</TEXT>
