<HEADLINE>
FT  21 MAY 94 / Venezuela sale setback
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOSEPH MANN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CARACAS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The government of President Rafael Caldera received a setback yesterday when
it failed to auction off a state-owned airline, Aeropostal, in its first
effort at privatisation, Joseph Mann writes from Caracas. Nine international
groups had qualified to bid, but only three - American Airlines, Aces of
Colombia, and a financial group headed by Venezuela's Progreso Mercado de
Capitales - sent repesentatives. Specific offers were not made public, but
the three groups told the government the base price of Dollars 62m was too
high, and they were concerned about limitations on foreign exchange sales.
</TEXT>
