<HEADLINE>
FT  21 MAY 94 / Chinese inflation at 22%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TONY WALKER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BEIJING
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
China's inflation rate was 21.7 a year in April, prompting calls for
continued tight controls on credit, Tony Walker writes from Beijing. The
state statistical bureau urged the government to 'keep a firm grip on the
economy to ensure a balance between supply and demand of goods in the
market'. April's inflation rate was marginally lower than that of March.
